    "body": "**Godot version:**\r\nadd3a825f0cb0c82026694b084f883f6f70be641\r\n\r\n**OS/device including version:**\r\nWin10\r\n\r\n**Issue description:**\r\nThere is a problem that occurred with buttons, for example, with these (from VisualScript):\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3036176/103569016-a2ba8500-4ed7-11eb-8a42-0700d84ef729.png)\r\nThey cause editor crash when the window of the other app is focused on the foreground instead of Godot Editor and the user clicks on one of these buttons without focusing on Godot Editor first.\r\n\r\nMake sure that `Single Window Mode` is disabled in the Editor Settings.\r\n\r\nIn the case of these buttons the crash happens at this line:\r\nhttps://github.com/godotengine/godot/blob/add3a825f0cb0c82026694b084f883f6f70be641/modules/visual_script/visual_script_editor.cpp#L1399\r\ndue to `ti` becomes null.\r\n\r\n**Steps to reproduce:**\r\nOpen Godot\r\nOpen VisualScript\r\nOpen another app (notepad for example)\r\nPress button\r\n\r\n**Minimal reproduction project:**\r\nBetter demonstration:\r\n![crash](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/3036176/103569523-82d79100-4ed8-11eb-88dc-0f938db2923a.gif)\r\n\r\n",
